chemlambda demos

    The exploded 20-quine (approx 25 sec).
    The main atoms appear far from the center of the picture, the external bonds appear close to the center of the picture, and the ports appear as dots inside the external bonds. The internal bonds appear as long and thin segments.
    How is done: see README.md. Use "bash quiner.sh" and choose 20_quine.mol/
    Use quiner.awk with bond_int=1; bond_ext=4; (around line 160). This will make the external bonds much thicker and shorter than the inner bonds. Edit the file firstpart_q.txt and modify it to have the following: .charge(-80) .gravity(.98) .linkStrength(2.8) . If needed play with .linkdistance (specifically with the number which multiplies d.bond). Finally, add .transition() .delay(1000) .attr("r", 2); just before node.exit().remove(); .
